articles.title: Australia begins cleanup after floods kill 5, strand thousands - Al Jazeera
articles.description: Hundreds of residents remain in evacuation centres, with 52 rescues made overnight despite conditions easing.
articles.content:
Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has announced the start of a cleanup operation in eastern Australia after record-breaking floods killed five people and stranded tens of thousands of people.
